Unsolved Practical: Create an HTML document that includes a section with multiple card elements representing different articles. Use CSS to style these cards as follows:
•	Apply padding, margin, border, and border-radius to all card elements.
•	Ensure that the card elements have a fixed width of 300 pixels and are horizontally centered within the viewport.
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
	<title>Article Cards</title>
	<link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
	<div class="card-container">
		<div class="card">
			<h2 Article 1</h2>
			<p>Children's day.</p>
			<button>Read More</button>
		</div>
		
		<div class="card">
			<h2>Article 2</h2>
			<p>Republic day.</p>
			<button>Read More</button>
		</div>
		
		<div class="card">
			<h2>Article 3</h2>
			<p>Independence day.</p>
			<button>Read More</button>
		</div>
	</div>
</body>
</html>


body {
	font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
	background-color: #f0f0f0;
}

.card-container {
	display: flex;
	justify-content: center;
	flex-wrap: wrap;
	gap: 20px;
	padding: 40px;
}

.card {
	background-color: #fff;
	padding: 20px;
	margin: 10px;
	border: 1px solid #ddd;
	border-radius: 10px;
	width: 300px;
	box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
}

.card h2 {
	margin-top: 0;
}

.card p {
	margin-bottom: 20px;
}

.card button {
	background-color: #4CAF50;
	color: #fff;
	padding: 10px 20px;
	border: none;
	border-radius: 5px;
	cursor: pointer;
}

.card button:hover {
	background-color: #3e8e41;
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
	.card-container {
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
	}
}
